1
00:01:57,923 --> 00:01:59,788
I love you, Billy.

2
00:02:03,729 --> 00:02:06,061
I love you too, Mommy.

3
00:02:12,438 --> 00:02:13,803
Night-night.

4
00:02:16,942 --> 00:02:18,341
Sleep tight.

5
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,771
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

6
00:02:25,518 --> 00:02:28,976
I'll see you in the morning light.

7
00:02:39,832 --> 00:02:41,493
I love you.

8
00:03:03,556 --> 00:03:06,024
They're going to make me
an assistant art director.

9
00:03:06,192 --> 00:03:06,783
So Kenny says:

10
00:03:07,026 --> 00:03:09,517
"You get yourself a Burberry coat.

11
00:03:09,795 --> 00:03:13,390
If you're gonna be Madison Avenue,
you have to look it."

12
00:03:13,632 --> 00:03:16,192
Saturday afternoon, I go out,
and it's cold.

13
00:03:16,468 --> 00:03:19,460
I go to this place
that specializes in Burberrys...

14
00:03:19,705 --> 00:03:22,469
and say, "I want a Burberry coat,
37 short."

15
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:25,575
They put it on,
and I look beautiful in it.

16
00:03:25,844 --> 00:03:27,004
I say, "I'll buy it."

17
00:03:27,213 --> 00:03:29,408
And right then, I start to sweat.

18
00:03:29,682 --> 00:03:33,709
I take my checkbook out, start to
sign the check, and my hand shakes...

19
00:03:33,986 --> 00:03:35,749
because I'm so scared.

20
00:03:36,021 --> 00:03:37,488
- Good night.
- Where you going?

21
00:03:37,723 --> 00:03:41,557
- I gotta get home.
- Oh, Jesus, I gotta go.

22
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:43,091
Okay, so let me finish.

23
00:03:43,362 --> 00:03:45,887
So I sign it,
and my hand starts shaking...

24
00:03:47,399 --> 00:03:50,994
Who is this? Danny, right?
Taxi!

25
00:03:51,237 --> 00:03:55,571
- Come on, I gotta tell you something.
- I can't. I gotta get home.

26
00:03:55,841 --> 00:03:58,503
Gotta talk to you
about something important.

27
00:03:58,744 --> 00:04:02,236
I'm putting you in charge
of the Mid-Atlantic account.

28
00:04:24,036 --> 00:04:27,164
By the end of the year, we'll
have them up to 10 million.

29
00:04:27,373 --> 00:04:30,604
If this campaign works out the way
I know it will...

30
00:04:30,876 --> 00:04:32,741
they'll offer me a partnership.

31
00:04:32,945 --> 00:04:34,378
That's terrific!

32
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:38,880
When that happens, I just want you
to know I'm taking you along.

33
00:04:40,252 --> 00:04:44,211
Wow! Wow! That's terrific.

34
00:05:01,774 --> 00:05:03,765
Joanna.

35
00:05:04,343 --> 00:05:06,072
I'm home.

36
00:05:09,148 --> 00:05:12,481
I forgot my keys. I gotta call
the office before they go.

37
00:05:12,751 --> 00:05:16,243
Jo, you're gonna be real proud
of me. I got good news.

38
00:05:18,757 --> 00:05:21,658
- Ted.
- One second. Let me just do this.

39
00:05:25,331 --> 00:05:28,596
You know Jack Edwards in accounting?
He committed suicide.

40
00:05:28,834 --> 00:05:30,927
Yeah, hi. Ted Kramer.

41
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:35,038
I gotta get those photos from
the retoucher by tomorrow morning.

42
00:05:35,274 --> 00:05:37,970
- I'm leaving you.
- Honey, please. I can't hear.

43
00:05:39,645 --> 00:05:42,478
Okay, you too. Thanks a lot.
See you tomorrow.

44
00:05:43,148 --> 00:05:44,547
Did you guys eat?

45
00:05:44,817 --> 00:05:45,817
I'm leaving you.

46
00:05:48,821 --> 00:05:50,618
Here are my keys.

47
00:05:50,823 --> 00:05:53,951
Here's my American Express,
my Bloomingdale's card...

48
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:58,027
my checkbook. I've taken
$2000 out of our savings account.

49
00:05:58,230 --> 00:06:00,494
That's what I had when we got married.

50
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:03,497
- Is this a joke?
- Here's the cleaning, laundry ticket.

51
00:06:03,736 --> 00:06:05,897
You can pick them both up
on Saturday.

52
00:06:06,138 --> 00:06:08,629
- You. You have to pick them up.
- What's wrong?

53
00:06:08,874 --> 00:06:12,674
I paid the rent, the Con Ed bill,
and the phone bill, so...

54
00:06:12,911 --> 00:06:14,708
You really pick your times to...

55
00:06:18,884 --> 00:06:22,752
I'm sorry I was late, but I was
busy making a living, all right?

56
00:06:23,555 --> 00:06:26,820
Come on, okay? Can we stop now?

57
00:06:27,092 --> 00:06:29,219
So that's everything.

58
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:36,094
Enough, enough. All right?

59
00:06:36,402 --> 00:06:38,393
What are you doing?

60
00:06:38,704 --> 00:06:42,231
Where are you going? Just tell me
what I did that's so terrible.

61
00:06:42,541 --> 00:06:43,872
- It's not you.
- Then what?

62
00:06:44,076 --> 00:06:46,101
It's me. It's my fault.

63
00:06:46,578 --> 00:06:48,068
You married the wrong person.

64
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,748
- I can't hack it.
- Let's just go inside.

65
00:06:51,016 --> 00:06:53,075
I can't, I tried.
I swear...

66
00:06:53,352 --> 00:06:56,185
Joanna, please, just... I'm sorry.

67
00:06:56,455 --> 00:07:01,552
- No, please don't make me go in there.
- I just want to talk.

68
00:07:01,794 --> 00:07:04,354
If you do, I swear, one day...

69
00:07:04,596 --> 00:07:07,087
I'll go right out the window.
- Oh, please.

70
00:07:07,366 --> 00:07:09,630
Come on, now. What about Billy?

71
00:07:13,572 --> 00:07:16,973
I'm not taking him with me.
I'm no good for him.

72
00:07:17,476 --> 00:07:18,909
I'm terrible with him.

73
00:07:19,211 --> 00:07:21,975
I have no patience.

74
00:07:22,214 --> 00:07:24,273
He's better off without me.

75
00:07:26,485 --> 00:07:27,952
Joanna, please.

76
00:07:32,825 --> 00:07:35,123
And I don't love you anymore.

77
00:07:37,129 --> 00:07:39,120
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

78
00:08:13,532 --> 00:08:16,831
Hi, Margaret. This is Ted.
Is my wife there?

79
00:08:17,035 --> 00:08:20,198
Yeah. Joanna come in?

80
00:08:20,506 --> 00:08:24,772
We had a little fight. I thought
she might have stopped by.

81
00:08:24,977 --> 00:08:28,310
If she comes in, tell her to come up
or just give me a ring.

82
00:08:30,215 --> 00:08:34,345
Don't worry. She didn't take
her suitcase. She won't get very far.

83
00:08:35,521 --> 00:08:38,854
I got work to do.
If she comes in, tell her to call me.

84
00:08:45,964 --> 00:08:47,488
It's about time.

85
00:08:50,536 --> 00:08:53,403
Joanna, that's the most insensitive...
Hi, Margaret.

86
00:08:53,672 --> 00:08:57,506
- She packed a suitcase?
- Look, it's nothing serious, really.

87
00:08:57,743 --> 00:08:59,711
She tell you where she was going?

88
00:08:59,978 --> 00:09:02,708
- You tell me.
- How would I know? I wasn't here.

89
00:09:02,981 --> 00:09:06,473
Clearly, you two had many
talks about my shortcomings...

90
00:09:06,718 --> 00:09:09,710
which I haven't been privy to.
And I'd love to talk...

91
00:09:09,988 --> 00:09:13,219
but I have a major presentation
in the morning...

92
00:09:13,492 --> 00:09:16,325
and I gotta get my work done.
So please allow me...

93
00:09:16,562 --> 00:09:19,190
You don't realize
we have a serious problem.

94
00:09:19,398 --> 00:09:22,367
Wrong. Me. I got the problem.
All you gotta do is...

95
00:09:22,601 --> 00:09:25,001
go out the door and go back to bed.

96
00:09:25,437 --> 00:09:27,928
- The fact is...
- For six months...

97
00:09:28,206 --> 00:09:31,767
I've been spitting blood to get
this agency its biggest account.

98
00:09:32,044 --> 00:09:34,103
And at five, we got it.

99
00:09:34,947 --> 00:09:39,407
At eight, the vice president tells me
I'll be the next creative director.

100
00:09:39,618 --> 00:09:42,212
I come through this door
to share with my wife...

101
00:09:42,421 --> 00:09:46,187
one of the five best days
of my life, and she looks at me...

102
00:09:46,425 --> 00:09:49,019
and tells me she doesn't want
to live with me!

103
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:57,127
Can't you understand
what she's done to me?

104
00:09:59,104 --> 00:10:02,596
She loused up one of the five
best days of your life.

105
00:10:06,478 --> 00:10:08,878
You're terrific. Boy, you're...

106
00:10:09,114 --> 00:10:11,105
Thanks very much, really.

107
00:10:12,784 --> 00:10:14,308
Sisterhood.

108
00:10:14,553 --> 00:10:16,783
Thank you for coming
to cheer me up, but...

109
00:10:17,122 --> 00:10:19,090
I didn't come to cheer you up.

110
00:10:19,391 --> 00:10:21,256
I'm concerned about Joanna.

111
00:10:21,793 --> 00:10:25,285
Maybe you can be concerned
in the privacy of your own apartment.

112
00:10:26,298 --> 00:10:30,632
Joanna and I never had any problems
until you and Charley split up.

113
00:10:30,902 --> 00:10:32,836
Oh, I don't believe you.

114
00:10:33,105 --> 00:10:34,902
Just tell me the truth, okay?

115
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:36,801
Did you set her up to this?

116
00:10:37,075 --> 00:10:38,975
No, I didn't put her up to this.

117
00:10:39,244 --> 00:10:41,678
- Give her a little pep talk?
- No, I didn't.

118
00:10:41,913 --> 00:10:43,904
Joanna and I talk a great deal.

119
00:10:44,149 --> 00:10:46,276
And Joanna is a very unhappy woman.

120
00:10:46,518 --> 00:10:51,012
And it took a lot of courage for her
to walk out of here.

121
00:10:51,256 --> 00:10:54,282
How much courage does it take
to walk out on your kid?

122
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:10,000
Where's Mommy?

123
00:12:10,268 --> 00:12:11,860
- What?
- Where's Mommy?

124
00:12:12,104 --> 00:12:13,537
What time is it?

125
00:12:14,773 --> 00:12:19,608
The little hand's on the 7, the big
hand's on the 9. Where's Mommy?

126
00:12:21,446 --> 00:12:26,509
Oh, God. Okay, I'm gonna tell you.
You want to know where Mommy is?

127
00:12:26,752 --> 00:12:30,051
- She's supposed to take me to school.
- She told me to do it.

128
00:12:30,255 --> 00:12:32,223
Okay, I'll tell you where she went.

129
00:12:32,424 --> 00:12:36,190
You know when you and your friends
don't get along and fight?

130
00:12:36,394 --> 00:12:38,954
And you want to go and be alone
for a while?

131
00:12:39,197 --> 00:12:41,859
Sometimes Mommy and Daddy
don't get along...

132
00:12:42,067 --> 00:12:45,867
and one of them wants to go
and be by themselves for a while.

133
00:12:46,071 --> 00:12:48,403
- When is Mommy coming back?
- Soon.

134
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:52,132
Now we are gonna have breakfast!
Okay? Just you and me.

135
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:54,537
- What do you want?
- French toast.

136
00:12:54,946 --> 00:12:56,937
You want French toast, you got it.

137
00:12:57,149 --> 00:13:00,312
Put up a little water for Daddy
to have some coffee.

138
00:13:00,552 --> 00:13:03,578
We got how many eggs?
Two for you and two for me.

139
00:13:03,822 --> 00:13:04,880
We got milk.

140
00:13:05,123 --> 00:13:06,590
We got butter.

141
00:13:06,792 --> 00:13:08,589
We got $5.

142
00:13:08,794 --> 00:13:11,285
I got $5.
Here, you sit here.

143
00:13:12,097 --> 00:13:14,895
Okay, can you be
my number one helper?

144
00:13:16,668 --> 00:13:17,896
Watch this. One hand.

145
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:20,069
Here we go.

146
00:13:20,272 --> 00:13:23,139
Did you know that all
the best chefs are men?

147
00:13:23,341 --> 00:13:26,504
Isn't this terrific?
We gotta do this more often.

148
00:13:26,745 --> 00:13:29,236
- You dropped some shell in it.
- That's okay.

149
00:13:29,648 --> 00:13:33,084
Makes it crunchier.
You like it crunchy, don't you?

150
00:13:33,285 --> 00:13:37,153
Why don't you beat them,
and I'll get everything else going.

151
00:13:37,422 --> 00:13:39,356
- What time is school?
- 8:30.

152
00:13:39,658 --> 00:13:43,788
Gotta get the show on the road.
I gotta shower, shave and shampoo.

153
00:13:44,029 --> 00:13:45,155
I got people to see.

154
00:13:45,363 --> 00:13:47,923
And Daddy's gotta bring home
the bacon...

155
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:49,633
and he's gotta cook it.

156
00:13:50,035 --> 00:13:53,027
We're having a good time!
Where does Mommy keep the..?

157
00:13:53,505 --> 00:13:55,632
- In the stove.
- The pan. The stove.

158
00:13:57,876 --> 00:13:59,503
First, we need a nice fire.

159
00:14:00,345 --> 00:14:02,438
No, you're not doing it right.

160
00:14:02,681 --> 00:14:06,117
Look, you gotta do it fast. See?
It's the wrist.

161
00:14:06,351 --> 00:14:08,216
So the gucky part dissolves.

162
00:14:08,453 --> 00:14:12,287
Then you take the bread, and we...

163
00:14:12,490 --> 00:14:14,185
We...

164
00:14:15,126 --> 00:14:18,289
We fold the French toast.
That's what we do.

165
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:22,022
- I think you forgot milk.
- I didn't. Milk comes last.

166
00:14:23,301 --> 00:14:25,963
When you're having a good time
you forget things.

167
00:14:26,671 --> 00:14:29,902
I just wanted to see
if you're paying attention.

168
00:14:30,408 --> 00:14:33,900
Fun, isn't it? When's the last
time Mommy let you in the kitchen?

169
00:14:34,212 --> 00:14:35,645
I don't like it in pieces.

170
00:14:35,881 --> 00:14:39,977
It tastes the same whether it's in
pieces or whole. Bread is bread.

171
00:14:40,318 --> 00:14:42,650
Besides, French toast
is always folded.

172
00:14:42,888 --> 00:14:46,085
In the best restaurants,
you see folded French toast.

173
00:14:46,424 --> 00:14:48,255
You get more bites that way.

174
00:14:50,095 --> 00:14:53,326
And while that's going,
Daddy's gonna make coffee.

175
00:14:53,598 --> 00:14:55,156
You having a good time?

176
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:58,996
I don't remember the last
time I had such a good time.

177
00:14:59,905 --> 00:15:01,770
Daddy's gonna make himself coffee.

178
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:04,440
- That's too much!
- No, I like it strong.

179
00:15:04,709 --> 00:15:06,836
Mommy always makes it too weak.

180
00:15:09,047 --> 00:15:11,015
Can I have some orange juice?

181
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:14,182
Right. One OJ coming up
for the kid.

182
00:15:16,688 --> 00:15:18,121
Daddy, it's burning!

183
00:15:18,957 --> 00:15:20,584
- What?
- It's burning!

184
00:15:22,527 --> 00:15:25,519
Damn it! Goddamn her!

185
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:30,430
Oh, shit.

186
00:15:32,604 --> 00:15:36,404
Just take it easy.
Everything is fine. We're terrific.

187
00:15:36,641 --> 00:15:38,108
Just...

188
00:15:39,477 --> 00:15:42,708
Just take it easy.
Nothing is the matter.

189
00:15:46,418 --> 00:15:47,817
- What?
- Your hand's sweaty.

190
00:15:48,086 --> 00:15:50,611
- When's Mommy coming back?
- Soon. I told you.

191
00:15:50,889 --> 00:15:54,222
- Is she gonna pick me up?
- Probably. If she doesn't, I will.

192
00:15:54,459 --> 00:15:56,324
- What if you forget?
- I won't.

193
00:15:56,594 --> 00:15:59,893
- What if you get run over?
- Mommy will pick you up.

194
00:16:00,131 --> 00:16:02,292
- Miss! What grade are you in?
- First.

195
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,060
This is Billy Kramer.
He's in first grade.

196
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:07,670
Take care of him. I gotta
get a taxi, I'm late. Taxi!

197
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,907
Taxi!

198
00:16:12,644 --> 00:16:15,511
- Congratulations about Mid-Atlantic.
- Thanks.

199
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:19,181
- Congratulations.
- Is the stuff back from the retoucher?

200
00:16:19,417 --> 00:16:21,749
- Great news, Ted.
- Thanks a lot.

201
00:16:21,987 --> 00:16:24,455
Morning. 11:00, meeting
with Airwick...

202
00:16:24,689 --> 00:16:27,954
- Where's the stuff from the retoucher?
- Right here.

203
00:16:28,626 --> 00:16:30,025
- Did my wife call?
- No.

204
00:16:30,295 --> 00:16:33,594
You're gonna have to cancel
the Airwick at 11:30.

205
00:17:04,796 --> 00:17:08,027
She's never gone this far before,
but in the past...

206
00:17:08,299 --> 00:17:11,132
I've known
when she's upset because...

207
00:17:11,369 --> 00:17:13,030
she gets very quiet.

208
00:17:13,304 --> 00:17:16,831
Our pattern has been that I've said,
"What's the matter?"...

209
00:17:17,042 --> 00:17:18,907
and she'll kind of sit on it.

210
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:22,236
But in the last few weeks,
maybe couple of months...

211
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:26,416
since we've been going crazy
with this account, I've been remiss.

212
00:17:26,684 --> 00:17:32,020
And I just didn't look at the writing
on the wall, so she's kind of...

213
00:17:32,557 --> 00:17:36,152
I think this is a way
of making me stop, look and say:

214
00:17:36,394 --> 00:17:38,521
"I'm as important as your work."

215
00:17:40,832 --> 00:17:42,857
Is there another guy?

216
00:17:44,869 --> 00:17:47,599
I don't think so.
She's not the type.

217
00:17:47,906 --> 00:17:50,739
She's got this friend, Margaret,
downstairs...

218
00:17:51,443 --> 00:17:55,743
you know, women's lib.
I think they may have cooked this up.

219
00:17:56,781 --> 00:17:57,839
It worked.

220
00:17:59,184 --> 00:18:00,617
I'm going crazy!

221
00:18:00,852 --> 00:18:03,047
Look, not to worry.

222
00:18:03,254 --> 00:18:04,846
She'll be back.

223
00:18:05,056 --> 00:18:07,422
I didn't know it would happen to me!

224
00:18:08,426 --> 00:18:09,950
Don't let it get you down.

225
00:18:10,195 --> 00:18:13,631
I know she'll be back.
I'm terrific, really.

226
00:18:16,234 --> 00:18:19,101
- You do have a problem, Ted.
- Yeah, what's that?

227
00:18:21,973 --> 00:18:23,907
What are you gonna do about Billy?

228
00:18:25,643 --> 00:18:29,602
This just happened last night.
I'm sure when Joanna comes back...

229
00:18:29,881 --> 00:18:32,076
It's none of my business.
I'll butt out.

230
00:18:32,283 --> 00:18:34,911
Listen, I want to hear your thoughts.

231
00:18:35,153 --> 00:18:38,316
I appreciate you
taking the time to talk to me.

232
00:18:39,057 --> 00:18:43,153
May sound a little rough, but...

233
00:18:43,428 --> 00:18:47,660
I think you ought to send Billy away
to stay with relatives for a while.

234
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:50,624
You mean, until Joanna comes back?

235
00:18:51,436 --> 00:18:53,734
Suppose Joanna doesn't come back?

236
00:18:57,008 --> 00:18:58,737
Gee, I don't know...

237
00:18:58,977 --> 00:19:00,501
Ted, listen to me.

238
00:19:00,778 --> 00:19:06,080
I just told the boys upstairs you're
handling the Mid-Atlantic account.

239
00:19:06,284 --> 00:19:10,846
You know? A gig like that comes
along once every five, six years.

240
00:19:11,156 --> 00:19:15,422
There's guys here eating their hearts
out because I gave that spot to you.

241
00:19:15,627 --> 00:19:19,028
This is important. Don't blow this.

242
00:19:19,297 --> 00:19:23,097
I gotta depend on you. I gotta count
on you for 110 percent...

243
00:19:23,635 --> 00:19:27,696
7 days a week, 24 hours a day.
I gotta have that.

244
00:19:28,006 --> 00:19:31,442
I can't be concerned about you
worrying about a kid.

245
00:19:31,776 --> 00:19:35,644
First, you can count on me
25 hours a day, 8 days a week.

246
00:19:35,847 --> 00:19:37,712
Because I'm not a loser, Jim.

247
00:19:37,982 --> 00:19:40,849
I never let anything at home
come into the office.

248
00:19:41,119 --> 00:19:43,383
You asked me to unload in this office.

249
00:19:43,655 --> 00:19:47,318
When I go outside, I'm on top of it.
I want you to know that.

250
00:19:47,525 --> 00:19:49,993
I'm a survivor.

251
00:19:50,195 --> 00:19:54,029
You've given me a shot here.
I'm not gonna let anything blow it.

252
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:56,898
Okay?

253
00:19:59,237 --> 00:20:02,138
Let's have a drink later.
I'm all right. I gotta...

254
00:20:02,373 --> 00:20:04,671
blow smoke up Airwick's ass, 11:00.

255
00:20:04,876 --> 00:20:06,537
I'm all right!

256
00:20:06,744 --> 00:20:08,211
You don't worry.

257
00:20:08,413 --> 00:20:09,812
Thank you.

258
00:20:10,815 --> 00:20:12,976
I love you, you bastard.

259
00:20:17,822 --> 00:20:20,518
Daddy?

260
00:20:20,758 --> 00:20:22,555
Daddy?

261
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:29,427
Yeah, honey, just wait a second.
I just want to finish this idea.

262
00:20:29,701 --> 00:20:32,431
Let me get this copy done,
and then I'll talk.

263
00:20:32,737 --> 00:20:37,003
What time is it when an elephant
sits on your fence?

264
00:20:38,343 --> 00:20:40,504
Time to get a new fence.

265
00:20:43,948 --> 00:20:46,610
Honey, please...
I just got this sentence.

266
00:20:47,018 --> 00:20:48,280
Daddy! Daddy!

267
00:20:49,187 --> 00:20:50,518
Goddamn it! Goddamn it!

268
00:20:50,722 --> 00:20:53,953
Get over there and sit
on that couch and don't move!

269
00:20:54,225 --> 00:20:56,887
I knew this was gonna happen!
I knew it!

270
00:20:57,128 --> 00:21:00,689
Who told you not to drink
this stuff here?

271
00:21:01,399 --> 00:21:02,866
- Sorry.
- Yeah, you're sorry.

272
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:05,763
Told you to keep that juice
in the dining room!

273
00:21:06,604 --> 00:21:07,798
Sorry.

274
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:11,903
Who took you to the park, gave you
everything you wanted?

275
00:21:12,143 --> 00:21:14,373
- Who bought you an ice cream?
- You.

276
00:21:14,612 --> 00:21:18,605
And who promised Daddy that when
we got home, you'd let him work?

277
00:21:20,051 --> 00:21:23,248
- That's ruined. I can't fix that.
- Sorry.

278
00:21:28,793 --> 00:21:32,058
It's past your bedtime.
Why don't you go to sleep?

279
00:21:37,735 --> 00:21:40,329
And brush your teeth
and flush the toilet.

280
00:21:45,810 --> 00:21:48,745
- Paper towels. What else?
- We need detergent.

281
00:21:48,980 --> 00:21:50,004
All right.

282
00:21:50,248 --> 00:21:53,513
No, Mommy buys the kind
with the orange circles on it.

283
00:21:53,785 --> 00:21:56,777
- There's no difference.
- Mom said it was the best.

284
00:22:01,459 --> 00:22:03,324
- Let's go.
- Get the pink stuff.

285
00:22:05,630 --> 00:22:06,927
All right, come on.

286
00:22:07,165 --> 00:22:09,759
Okay. That's it.

287
00:22:10,835 --> 00:22:12,928
We need some cereal.

288
00:22:13,671 --> 00:22:15,366
Okay, what color?

289
00:22:25,116 --> 00:22:27,482
Hey, Billy!

290
00:22:27,685 --> 00:22:31,143
Billy! Told you Mommy would write
before the week was up.

291
00:22:31,456 --> 00:22:35,392
- When is she coming back?
- That's what we're gonna find out now.

292
00:22:36,461 --> 00:22:39,157
Okay. Let's read it.

293
00:22:44,969 --> 00:22:47,699
"My dearest, sweet Billy."

294
00:22:50,308 --> 00:22:51,866
That's you.

295
00:22:54,178 --> 00:22:56,237
"Mommy has gone away."

296
00:22:56,514 --> 00:22:58,982
Sometimes in the world...

297
00:22:59,183 --> 00:23:00,514
daddies go away...

298
00:23:00,818 --> 00:23:03,378
and mommies bring up
their little boys.

299
00:23:03,654 --> 00:23:06,521
But sometimes, a mommy
can go away too...

300
00:23:06,758 --> 00:23:09,852
and you have your daddy
to bring you up.

301
00:23:10,161 --> 00:23:12,425
I have gone away
because I must find...

302
00:23:12,663 --> 00:23:16,531
something interesting to do
for myself in the world.

303
00:23:16,768 --> 00:23:19,430
Everybody has to, and so do I.

304
00:23:23,341 --> 00:23:27,937
Being your mommy was one thing,
but there are other things too...

305
00:23:28,212 --> 00:23:31,204
and this is what I have to do.

306
00:23:31,416 --> 00:23:33,850
I did not get a chance
to tell you this...

307
00:23:34,118 --> 00:23:36,848
and that is why
I'm writing you now.

308
00:23:37,088 --> 00:23:39,613
I will always be your mommy...

309
00:23:41,225 --> 00:23:43,625
and I will always love you.

310
00:23:44,362 --> 00:23:46,853
I just won't be your mommy
in the house...

311
00:23:47,064 --> 00:23:49,624
but I'll be your mommy
at the heart.

312
00:23:50,268 --> 00:23:54,136
"And now I must go
and be the person I have to be."

313
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:01,302
We'll read this another time.

314
00:24:01,546 --> 00:24:02,979
I don't care.

315
00:25:14,452 --> 00:25:16,352
- Good night, Jim.
- Come on in.

316
00:25:16,687 --> 00:25:18,882
- Have a drink.
- I can't, I'm late now.

317
00:25:19,123 --> 00:25:22,854
What's the rush? We're having
a party for Norman. Five years here.

318
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,152
Can you believe it?

319
00:25:24,395 --> 00:25:27,159
Wish I could, but I'm late.
I gotta pick up Billy.

320
00:25:27,365 --> 00:25:29,333
You know Jerry Hoover, in media?

321
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:31,459
Tell you something funny.

322
00:25:31,669 --> 00:25:33,296
Gotta go. See you Monday.

323
00:25:38,576 --> 00:25:40,203
Taxi!

324
00:25:41,078 --> 00:25:42,568
Taxi!

325
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:48,310
- Here, keep the change.
- Thanks.

326
00:26:06,237 --> 00:26:08,933
Hi, Mrs. Kline. I'm sorry I'm late.

327
00:26:09,206 --> 00:26:11,674
That's all right, but Billy is upset.

328
00:26:12,376 --> 00:26:14,367
Hey, how's it going, sport?

329
00:26:15,446 --> 00:26:18,779
I had a little trouble
getting away from the office.

330
00:26:19,083 --> 00:26:21,677
Sorry. Come on, let's get going.

331
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:25,546
Thanks for coming, Billy.
Oh, wait a minute.

332
00:26:25,790 --> 00:26:28,725
- Don't forget your goody bag.
- Thanks very much.

333
00:26:29,026 --> 00:26:30,618
- Bye.
- Thanks a lot.

334
00:26:30,861 --> 00:26:34,422
- So, did you have a lot of fun?
- You're late.

335
00:26:34,632 --> 00:26:37,430
- I'm not that late. Only 20 minutes.
- Want to bet?

336
00:26:38,869 --> 00:26:41,736
All the other mothers were there
before you.

337
00:26:44,775 --> 00:26:48,302
Why are you making such a big deal
of it? There was traffic.

338
00:26:50,948 --> 00:26:54,543
If you want to be a big boy...

339
00:26:54,785 --> 00:26:58,721
you learn that when somebody says
they're sorry...

340
00:26:58,923 --> 00:27:04,122
you don't hold a grudge
and make them feel bad for...

341
00:27:04,395 --> 00:27:07,330
a long time afterwards.

342
00:27:07,565 --> 00:27:09,226
Okay, go ahead.

343
00:27:12,403 --> 00:27:15,167
Don't eat with your fingers.
Come on, Billy.

344
00:27:15,406 --> 00:27:18,603
You know better than that.
Here.

345
00:27:18,843 --> 00:27:20,310
Use a fork.

346
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:26,115
Come on, come on.
Sit up, sit up, sit up.

347
00:27:26,984 --> 00:27:28,815
How was school today?

348
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:30,985
Same as usual.

349
00:27:31,188 --> 00:27:33,418
I see the Knicks finally won a game.

350
00:27:33,691 --> 00:27:35,488
I don't care.

351
00:27:35,693 --> 00:27:37,285
What do you mean?

352
00:27:37,528 --> 00:27:40,520
- I like Boston.
- Boston? Why do you like Boston?

353
00:27:41,032 --> 00:27:43,193
Because Mommy's from Boston.

354
00:27:47,805 --> 00:27:49,796
Sit up and try to eat. Come on.

355
00:27:50,041 --> 00:27:53,033
Can I be excused?
I want to go to bed.

356
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:54,675
Too much birthday cake?

357
00:27:54,879 --> 00:27:56,540
Yeah, I guess.

358
00:32:06,297 --> 00:32:07,764
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

359
00:32:08,065 --> 00:32:09,362
Louise, give me a hand.

360
00:32:09,566 --> 00:32:10,965
You're 15 minutes late.

361
00:32:11,268 --> 00:32:13,736
- Mr. O'Connor is very upset.
- This all of it?

362
00:32:13,971 --> 00:32:18,067
- Yes. Do you want your mail now?
- No, just give me the messages.

363
00:32:18,309 --> 00:32:21,710
Remind me to get
a Crying Chrissie doll at lunch.

364
00:32:21,946 --> 00:32:23,277
Okay, okay.

365
00:32:23,547 --> 00:32:24,547
Sorry I'm late.

366
00:32:24,715 --> 00:32:28,913
And there's a PTA meeting
at the school on Tuesday at 4.

367
00:32:31,588 --> 00:32:32,919
Right, thanks.

368
00:32:33,157 --> 00:32:35,819
Put the chicken in the refrigerator.

369
00:32:38,128 --> 00:32:39,891
Know who Charley's seeing now?

370
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:41,130
Who?

371
00:32:41,432 --> 00:32:45,630
A divorced woman with two little girls
the same age as Kim and Petey.

372
00:32:45,903 --> 00:32:47,768
- Are you kidding?
- No.

373
00:32:48,005 --> 00:32:49,063
How do you know?

374
00:32:49,273 --> 00:32:51,138
I know.

375
00:32:51,342 --> 00:32:54,243
How long has it been since
you two broke up?

376
00:32:54,445 --> 00:32:55,445
Year and a half.

377
00:32:55,612 --> 00:32:57,807
That long?

378
00:32:58,115 --> 00:33:00,140
Did I ever tell you how sorry...

379
00:33:00,351 --> 00:33:03,445
how sad Joanna and I were
when you guys split?

380
00:33:04,421 --> 00:33:07,913
Look at that cute little boy
over there.

381
00:33:08,125 --> 00:33:10,423
You think you'll ever
get married again?

382
00:33:13,330 --> 00:33:15,264
- I mean, to anybody.
- No.

383
00:33:15,499 --> 00:33:16,864
Why?

384
00:33:18,369 --> 00:33:21,861
Maybe it's different if you don't
have children, but...

385
00:33:23,507 --> 00:33:27,637
even if Charley and I aren't living
together, and even if we're...

386
00:33:27,878 --> 00:33:32,941
sleeping with other people, even
if he were to get married again...

387
00:33:34,184 --> 00:33:35,845
he's still my husband...

388
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:39,180
and he's still the father of my
children and...

389
00:33:41,125 --> 00:33:45,061
That stuff about "till death do you
part," that's really true.

390
00:33:45,362 --> 00:33:48,957
Let's say Charley finishes
his midlife crisis...

391
00:33:49,166 --> 00:33:53,159
he's had it with his flings
and comes asking for forgiveness.

392
00:33:53,404 --> 00:33:55,031
What would you do?

393
00:33:59,143 --> 00:34:04,137
I think that if he really loved me...

394
00:34:04,381 --> 00:34:06,815
he wouldn't have let me
divorce him.

395
00:34:15,926 --> 00:34:18,190
You still think about him, don't you?

396
00:34:19,730 --> 00:34:21,755
Only all the time.

397
00:34:29,073 --> 00:34:31,541
- Think about Joanna?
- Never.

398
00:34:34,078 --> 00:34:35,909
Liar.

399
00:34:38,215 --> 00:34:40,274
Some pair, boy.

400
00:34:41,752 --> 00:34:43,014
I don't believe it.

401
00:34:43,253 --> 00:34:45,687
- You missed the closing.
- I'm sorry.

402
00:34:45,889 --> 00:34:50,189
Look, I gotta tell you something.
I'm getting very nervous here.

403
00:34:50,394 --> 00:34:53,557
Ever since your wife left you.
Is it eight months now?

404
00:34:53,797 --> 00:34:55,560
You're not getting any better.

405
00:34:55,799 --> 00:34:56,891
What do you mean?

406
00:34:57,134 --> 00:35:02,401
Look, I can't let your family problems
interfere with my responsibilities.

407
00:35:02,606 --> 00:35:03,868
I got a shop to run.

408
00:35:04,141 --> 00:35:07,736
I regret it, and I promise you
it will never happen again.

409
00:35:08,112 --> 00:35:09,272
Okay?

410
00:35:13,283 --> 00:35:14,477
Yeah?

411
00:35:16,587 --> 00:35:17,747
Yeah, wait a minute.

412
00:35:17,988 --> 00:35:20,252
- It's for you, pick up 461.
- Who is it?

413
00:35:20,491 --> 00:35:22,823
Pick up 461.

414
00:35:25,462 --> 00:35:26,793
Yeah?

415
00:35:27,731 --> 00:35:30,131
Oh, hi, Billy. What's up?

416
00:35:30,667 --> 00:35:33,898
No, one hour of television a day.
That's the rule.

417
00:35:34,605 --> 00:35:35,799
No.

418
00:35:36,573 --> 00:35:40,509
I don't care what the other
mothers do, Billy. We made a deal.

419
00:35:40,811 --> 00:35:42,904
I can't talk now. I'm busy.

420
00:35:43,747 --> 00:35:47,513
We will talk about it tonight
when I get home, all right?

421
00:35:47,751 --> 00:35:50,413
Double chocolate chip. I remember.

422
00:35:54,691 --> 00:35:56,249
I'm getting very nervous.

423
00:36:03,133 --> 00:36:05,328
Put that down and eat your dinner.

424
00:36:05,602 --> 00:36:07,035
What is this crap?

425
00:36:07,871 --> 00:36:10,135
- It's Salisbury steak.
- I hate it.

426
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:12,865
You had it last week and you loved it.

427
00:36:13,110 --> 00:36:16,602
No, I didn't. I hate the brown
stuff. It's gross.

428
00:36:16,813 --> 00:36:19,213
- It's onions and gravy.
- I'm allergic to onions.

429
00:36:19,550 --> 00:36:21,882
You are not.
You had this last week...

430
00:36:22,219 --> 00:36:26,155
and I said it was my favorite and you
said, "It's my favorite too."

431
00:36:26,356 --> 00:36:28,051
- I did not.
- Yes, you did.

432
00:36:29,293 --> 00:36:30,555
It's regular hamburger.

433
00:36:30,861 --> 00:36:32,453
Take a bite. It's delicious.

434
00:36:34,531 --> 00:36:35,531
What's the matter?

435
00:36:35,799 --> 00:36:37,164
I'm gonna throw up.

436
00:36:37,401 --> 00:36:39,528
- No, you're not.
- It's yucky.

437
00:36:39,736 --> 00:36:42,671
It is not yucky, Billy. Eat it.

438
00:36:47,744 --> 00:36:50,577
Did you bring the chocolate chip
ice cream home?

439
00:36:51,848 --> 00:36:54,578
Yes, I brought the chocolate chip
ice cream home...

440
00:36:54,885 --> 00:36:58,321
and you can't have it until
you eat all your dinner...

441
00:36:59,156 --> 00:37:01,420
Where are you going?
Get back here now.

442
00:37:01,658 --> 00:37:03,057
Did you hear me?

443
00:37:03,327 --> 00:37:04,521
You'd better not do that.

444
00:37:05,362 --> 00:37:08,024
You'd better stop right there.
I'm warning you.

445
00:37:11,068 --> 00:37:12,092
Did you hear me?

446
00:37:14,571 --> 00:37:17,768
Now, you listen to me.
Don't be smart.

447
00:37:18,041 --> 00:37:20,441
Put that back until you finish
your dinner.

448
00:37:23,347 --> 00:37:26,282
If you take one bite out of that,
you're in trouble.

449
00:37:28,552 --> 00:37:31,180
Don't you dare.
Don't you dare do that.

450
00:37:31,421 --> 00:37:33,252
You hear me? Hold it right there.

451
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:38,493
You put that ice cream in your mouth
and you are in very big trouble.

452
00:37:38,762 --> 00:37:41,993
Don't you dare go anywhere
beyond that. Put it down.

453
00:37:42,199 --> 00:37:46,431
I am not going to say it again.
I am not going to say it again.

454
00:37:49,539 --> 00:37:50,767
You're hurting me!

455
00:37:51,475 --> 00:37:52,703
Don't you kick me.

456
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:56,508
- I hate you!
- You're no bargain either, pal.

457
00:37:56,713 --> 00:37:59,011
You are a spoiled little brat!

458
00:37:59,283 --> 00:38:02,013
- I hate you!
- I hate you back, you little shit!

459
00:38:02,319 --> 00:38:05,720
- I want my mommy!
- I'm all you've got.

460
00:38:06,957 --> 00:38:10,859
I want my mommy!

461
00:38:14,231 --> 00:38:16,825
I want my mommy!

462
00:38:22,906 --> 00:38:26,205
I want my mommy!

463
00:38:27,344 --> 00:38:29,141
Mommy...

464
00:39:22,799 --> 00:39:23,959
Daddy?

465
00:39:25,268 --> 00:39:26,268
Daddy?

466
00:39:26,570 --> 00:39:28,561
- Yeah?
- I'm sorry.

467
00:39:29,906 --> 00:39:31,237
I'm sorry too.

468
00:39:34,544 --> 00:39:37,308
I want you to go to sleep
because it's really late.

469
00:39:38,949 --> 00:39:40,041
Daddy?

470
00:39:40,784 --> 00:39:41,978
Now what is it?

471
00:39:42,819 --> 00:39:44,252
Are you going away?

472
00:39:45,222 --> 00:39:46,222
No.

473
00:39:46,790 --> 00:39:50,226
I'm staying here with you.
You can't get rid of me that easy.

474
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:53,754
That's why Mommy left, isn't it?
Because I was bad?

475
00:39:55,799 --> 00:39:57,164
Is that what you think?

476
00:39:58,902 --> 00:39:59,902
No.

477
00:40:01,171 --> 00:40:05,267
That's not it, Billy.
Your mom loves you very much...

478
00:40:05,475 --> 00:40:09,241
and the reason she left has
nothing to do with you.

479
00:40:11,248 --> 00:40:16,185
I don't know if this will make sense,
but I'll try to explain it to you.

480
00:40:19,589 --> 00:40:22,114
I think the reason why Mommy left...

481
00:40:23,093 --> 00:40:24,788
was because for a long time...

482
00:40:25,061 --> 00:40:30,158
I kept trying to make her be
a certain kind of person.

483
00:40:30,967 --> 00:40:35,927
A certain kind of wife that
I thought she was supposed to be.

484
00:40:36,173 --> 00:40:39,267
And she just wasn't like that.
She was...

485
00:40:40,477 --> 00:40:42,104
She just wasn't like that.

486
00:40:44,648 --> 00:40:49,745
I think that she tried for so long
to make me happy...

487
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:53,978
and when she couldn't,
she tried to talk to me about it.

488
00:40:54,658 --> 00:40:58,958
But I wasn't listening.
