00:58:23,047 --> 00:58:25,538
He comes in and pats me.
He comes to here.

741
00:58:25,783 --> 00:58:29,651
And he says, "Daddy, you've really
lost a lot of weight."

742
00:58:29,920 --> 00:58:33,879
He looks up at me and he says,
"And it's all gone to your nose."

743
00:58:36,227 --> 00:58:37,990
He was so cute. You know?

744
00:58:38,295 --> 00:58:39,295
You know, kids.

745
00:58:39,497 --> 00:58:41,465
It's delicious, want a taste?

746
00:58:41,665 --> 00:58:43,394
- I'm full.
- It's good.

747
00:58:43,667 --> 00:58:45,567
Listen, Ted...

748
00:58:45,770 --> 00:58:50,469
I had a call from a friend
of mine over at another agency.

749
00:58:51,609 --> 00:58:55,136
The Mid-Atlantic people have
invited them to pitch the account.

750
00:58:55,346 --> 00:58:56,404
Why?

751
00:58:56,614 --> 00:58:59,082
They're not happy
with what we're doing.

752
00:59:00,317 --> 00:59:03,809
I think you should have them over
and I'll give a little tap dance.

753
00:59:05,122 --> 00:59:06,987
I got Norman working on it.

754
00:59:07,258 --> 00:59:08,816
Norman?

755
00:59:11,796 --> 00:59:14,026
You taking me off the account?

756
00:59:16,100 --> 00:59:17,499
You don't like me anymore?

757
00:59:17,802 --> 00:59:19,667
It's not quite that simple.

758
00:59:22,473 --> 00:59:25,340
I think we're gonna have to
make a few changes here.

759
00:59:29,547 --> 00:59:31,174
You're firing me?

760
00:59:32,883 --> 00:59:35,113
Yeah, I'm letting you go, yes.

761
00:59:38,522 --> 00:59:39,522
Why?

762
00:59:39,623 --> 00:59:42,888
Now, look, Ted, this is
a very painful thing for me.

763
00:59:43,127 --> 00:59:47,188
I've been getting a lot of pressure
from the guys upstairs.

764
00:59:47,398 --> 00:59:49,332
There wasn't anything I could do.

765
00:59:49,533 --> 00:59:51,797
I think it's better this way.

766
00:59:52,002 --> 00:59:53,162
If I took your stripes...

767
00:59:53,404 --> 00:59:58,205
if I put you on a schlock account,
you'd hate it, and me for doing it.

768
00:59:58,476 --> 01:00:01,343
This way it's a clean break.
That's the best thing.

769
01:00:01,712 --> 01:00:04,203
You know my wife is fighting
for custody?

770
01:00:04,482 --> 01:00:06,814
You know that we're going to court?

771
01:00:07,084 --> 01:00:10,383
Do you know what my chances are
if I'm out of a job?

772
01:00:11,088 --> 01:00:13,215
I understand that you're upset...

773
01:00:13,424 --> 01:00:17,224
I don't want to beg, but I'm
asking you, please, as a friend.

774
01:00:18,362 --> 01:00:19,727
I'm asking you.

775
01:00:19,930 --> 01:00:23,559
You're an extremely bright guy.
You've got a hell of a talent.

776
01:00:23,767 --> 01:00:27,703
You're gonna land on your feet.
You're gonna survive.

777
01:00:27,938 --> 01:00:29,565
Teddy, look.

778
01:00:31,008 --> 01:00:33,101
I know you may be short on cash.

779
01:00:33,344 --> 01:00:35,778
No big hurry about paying this back.

780
01:00:36,180 --> 01:00:37,875
Shame on you.

781
01:01:30,467 --> 01:01:32,731
Daddy, the phone's ringing.

782
01:01:33,637 --> 01:01:34,797
<i>- Mr. Kramer?
- Yes.</i>

783
01:01:35,005 --> 01:01:37,132
<i>- Hold on for Mr. Shaunessy.
- Ted.</i>

784
01:01:37,408 --> 01:01:39,000
John. What's happening?

785
01:01:39,276 --> 01:01:43,110
They set the court date.
I just heard today it's January 9th.

786
01:01:43,314 --> 01:01:47,148
I gotta tell you something.
I got fired today. They laid me off.

787
01:01:50,120 --> 01:01:53,112
Yeah, I'm still here.
Ted, I won't lie to you.

788
01:01:53,357 --> 01:01:56,918
We don't have a hope of winning
if you're out of work.

789
01:01:58,028 --> 01:02:00,462
Yeah, listen, you tell that...

790
01:02:01,131 --> 01:02:04,259
You tell that party and you tell
that party's attorney...

791
01:02:04,501 --> 01:02:05,866
that I want a delay.

792
01:02:06,103 --> 01:02:07,832
Sorry, it's really too late.

793
01:02:08,472 --> 01:02:10,940
<i>- Fine. I'll have a job in 24 hours.
- How?</i>

794
01:02:11,175 --> 01:02:13,109
I'll have a job in 24 hours.

795
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:45,536
<i>This is the worst time
to look for work.</i>

796
01:02:45,809 --> 01:02:49,370
It's the holidays. We'll have
something for you by mid-February.

797
01:02:49,647 --> 01:02:51,877
- March, at the latest.
- I can't wait.

798
01:02:52,149 --> 01:02:54,811
Mr. Kramer, it's December 22.

799
01:02:55,185 --> 01:02:57,745
If you could just look
in your card catalogue.

800
01:03:02,860 --> 01:03:04,691
I'll take anything.

801
01:03:07,765 --> 01:03:10,928
There might be something
at Norman, Craig and Kummel.

802
01:03:11,168 --> 01:03:12,897
What is it?

803
01:03:13,170 --> 01:03:14,831
Something in the art department.

804
01:03:15,072 --> 01:03:16,403
You'd go back on the board.

805
01:03:16,607 --> 01:03:20,008
It's really a step down,
and a cut in salary of 5000.

806
01:03:20,210 --> 01:03:21,871
You'll be happier if you wait.

807
01:03:22,079 --> 01:03:26,038
Call them up, make an appointment
for me today at 4:00.

808
01:03:26,250 --> 01:03:27,842
It's the Friday before Christmas.

809
01:03:28,085 --> 01:03:29,382
It's still a workday.

810
01:03:29,787 --> 01:03:31,414
Nobody's gonna want to...

811
01:03:31,622 --> 01:03:33,351
Either you call them or I do.

812
01:03:33,557 --> 01:03:36,856
If I call them up, you don't get
a commission. Right?

813
01:03:37,094 --> 01:03:39,289
My, we are a hotshot, aren't we?

814
01:03:41,632 --> 01:03:42,724
Yes, we are.

815
01:03:49,139 --> 01:03:52,438
- Good afternoon.
- I'm Kramer. I have an appointment.

816
01:03:53,544 --> 01:03:55,569
I did all of the copy on that one.

817
01:03:58,649 --> 01:04:01,584
That was the most successful
ad campaign they ever had.

818
01:04:01,785 --> 01:04:05,380
I did the idea, the layout
and most of the copy on that one.

819
01:04:06,890 --> 01:04:09,984
Mr. Kramer, I must say,
this is very impressive.

820
01:04:10,561 --> 01:04:12,153
I'd like to get back to you.

821
01:04:12,429 --> 01:04:16,058
Is there someone I should see
before you come to your decision?

822
01:04:16,600 --> 01:04:18,568
Mr. Spencer, our creative director.

823
01:04:18,802 --> 01:04:20,793
Why don't you let me see him now?

824
01:04:21,505 --> 01:04:26,238
He's leaving on vacation. I'll set
something up the moment he gets back.

825
01:04:26,477 --> 01:04:28,308
- I think...
- Have a nice holiday.

826
01:04:28,612 --> 01:04:31,240
I'd like to see him before he leaves.

827
01:04:32,349 --> 01:04:35,750
- Mr. Kramer, I don't...
- I want this position very much.

828
01:04:38,856 --> 01:04:39,856
Wait here.

829
01:05:10,687 --> 01:05:12,314
Mr. Kramer, Mr. Spencer.

830
01:05:12,623 --> 01:05:14,614
- How do you do?
- You got 10 minutes.

831
01:05:17,561 --> 01:05:22,328
You do understand that the salary is
$4800 less than you were making?

832
01:05:22,633 --> 01:05:24,066
Yes, I understand.

833
01:05:24,301 --> 01:05:28,203
Why are you interested in a position
for which you're overqualified?

834
01:05:28,639 --> 01:05:29,697
I need the job.

835
01:05:30,541 --> 01:05:33,999
Let me think. I'll let Jack know
and he'll get in touch with you.

836
01:05:34,478 --> 01:05:35,968
This is a one-day offer.

837
01:05:36,180 --> 01:05:39,411
You saw my book,
you know I can handle the work.

838
01:05:39,683 --> 01:05:41,878
You're gonna have
to let me know today,

839
01:05:42,052 --> 01:05:43,713
not at the end of the holidays.

840
01:05:43,987 --> 01:05:46,717
If you want me,
make a decision right now.

841
01:05:53,597 --> 01:05:55,997
Could we talk privately for a moment?

842
01:05:56,233 --> 01:05:57,393
Yes, sir.

843
01:06:43,780 --> 01:06:48,376
Mr. Kramer, you got yourself a job.
Congratulations.

844
01:06:48,619 --> 01:06:49,916
Really?

845
01:06:51,889 --> 01:06:53,914
- Is he kidding?
- Welcome aboard.

846
01:06:54,157 --> 01:06:56,921
Thank you. Thank you very much.
Thanks.

847
01:07:15,646 --> 01:07:17,011
Merry Christmas.

848
01:07:30,427 --> 01:07:31,621
Come on.

849
01:07:36,133 --> 01:07:38,328
- What do you think?
- It's neat.

850
01:07:38,535 --> 01:07:40,935
- I told you.
- Where is everybody?

851
01:07:41,171 --> 01:07:45,801
It's Saturday, so very few people
come in because it's a day off.

852
01:07:46,276 --> 01:07:47,868
Okay, push "up."

853
01:07:51,315 --> 01:07:53,510
Push the top button.
Very top button.

854
01:07:53,784 --> 01:07:55,183
Go ahead, jump.

855
01:07:58,822 --> 01:08:00,050
- Look at that!
- Neat!

856
01:08:00,290 --> 01:08:01,689
You didn't know you were so high.

857
01:08:01,959 --> 01:08:04,689
What building is that?
That has the pointy top.

858
01:08:04,962 --> 01:08:06,452
That's the Chrysler.

859
01:08:06,730 --> 01:08:08,527
You proud of me?

860
01:08:08,832 --> 01:08:10,026
How'd you get this job?

861
01:08:10,300 --> 01:08:13,326
I told them I wanted it.
What's that say?

862
01:08:13,537 --> 01:08:14,561
It says "Kramer."

863
01:08:14,871 --> 01:08:16,839
Kramer. Who's that?

864
01:08:17,074 --> 01:08:19,008
- That's us.
- That's right.

865
01:08:19,209 --> 01:08:20,642
You want to see?

866
01:08:22,379 --> 01:08:24,404
Wow!

867
01:08:25,582 --> 01:08:28,346
- This is neat.
- You like it?

868
01:08:28,919 --> 01:08:30,147
Careful, careful.

869
01:08:30,387 --> 01:08:31,547
- I'm okay.
- Scare me.

870
01:08:31,755 --> 01:08:33,382
What's that building?

871
01:08:33,590 --> 01:08:36,320
That's the U.N. Building.
That's the East River.

872
01:08:36,560 --> 01:08:38,425
Look across there. You see that?

873
01:08:38,662 --> 01:08:41,324
That's Queens.
Look way, way down there.

874
01:08:41,565 --> 01:08:42,998
- Know what that is?
- What?

875
01:08:43,200 --> 01:08:45,896
- Brooklyn.
- Where you lived when you were a kid?

876
01:08:46,203 --> 01:08:49,001
That's right,
and this is where I work.

877
01:08:51,174 --> 01:08:53,165
Is this really your desk?

878
01:08:56,346 --> 01:08:58,177
Are you gonna get remarried?

879
01:08:58,382 --> 01:09:00,441
I hadn't thought about it.

880
01:09:00,951 --> 01:09:03,010
Are you gonna marry Phyllis?

881
01:09:03,220 --> 01:09:05,245
No, we're just good friends.

882
01:09:09,059 --> 01:09:11,721
Are you and Mom ever
gonna get remarried?

883
01:09:12,629 --> 01:09:15,257
No, Mommy and me will never
be remarried.

884
01:09:15,766 --> 01:09:19,031
I bet if she saw this,
she'd remarry you.

885
01:09:22,272 --> 01:09:24,467
You're a con artist. We made a deal.

886
01:09:24,775 --> 01:09:26,800
You take a bath every night...

887
01:09:27,044 --> 01:09:30,104
and you wash that filthy hair
twice a week, right?

888
01:09:30,547 --> 01:09:31,547
- Right?
- Yeah.

889
01:09:31,615 --> 01:09:32,877
Okay.

890
01:09:33,116 --> 01:09:34,447
Promise, or you're not going.

891
01:09:34,951 --> 01:09:37,613
Did I have to
when Mommy was here?

892
01:09:37,888 --> 01:09:40,550
I don't care what you had
to do when Mommy...

893
01:09:42,325 --> 01:09:45,556
Did I, Dad? Did I?

894
01:09:47,664 --> 01:09:48,926
Are you listening?

895
01:09:49,132 --> 01:09:51,965
We'll talk about it tonight
when I get home, okay?

896
01:09:52,169 --> 01:09:53,830
Come here, give me a kiss.

897
01:09:54,905 --> 01:09:57,237
- What?
- You're a terrific kid.

898
01:10:03,513 --> 01:10:05,344
He says, "There's the unicorn."

899
01:10:05,615 --> 01:10:08,277
And he goes underneath there,
and he says:

900
01:10:08,518 --> 01:10:10,748
"Crumbs, what's happening?

901
01:10:10,987 --> 01:10:12,614
The air supply has stopped.

902
01:10:12,923 --> 01:10:15,448
Thundering typhoons,
what are you doing?"

903
01:10:15,692 --> 01:10:18,024
"Resting. It's tiring work,
you know."

904
01:10:18,261 --> 01:10:19,751
What's the air supply?

905
01:10:19,996 --> 01:10:23,454
When you got two tanks on your back
and you can't get any air...

906
01:10:23,667 --> 01:10:25,862
you can drown,
so he's gotta have that.

907
01:10:26,169 --> 01:10:27,363
<i>Ted, John Shaunessy.</i>

908
01:10:27,604 --> 01:10:28,628
Hi, what's up?

909
01:10:28,839 --> 01:10:33,037
<i>I got a call from your wife's lawyer.
She wants to see the kid.</i>

910
01:10:33,443 --> 01:10:35,809
- She wants what?
- She's the mother.

911
01:10:36,012 --> 01:10:38,105
She's within her legal rights.

912
01:10:38,348 --> 01:10:42,546
<i>- How do I know she won't kidnap him?
- I don't think she'd bother...</i>

913
01:10:42,853 --> 01:10:45,117
suing if she's gonna kidnap him.

914
01:10:45,856 --> 01:10:48,723
Wait. I'm not so sure
about her mental health.

915
01:10:48,992 --> 01:10:52,291
<i>- What do you mean?
- She said she was seeing a shrink.</i>

916
01:10:52,496 --> 01:10:53,520
A psychiatrist.

917
01:10:53,730 --> 01:10:55,163
Did you see her talk to walls?

918
01:10:55,365 --> 01:10:56,957
<i>I'm just saying, you know.</i>

919
01:10:57,200 --> 01:10:59,566
I'm just saying you don't
have a choice.

920
01:10:59,836 --> 01:11:03,169
Have Billy at the boat pond
in Central Park, Saturday at 10.

921
01:11:03,406 --> 01:11:05,533
<i>- Do I have to?
- Yes.</i>

922
01:11:06,643 --> 01:11:08,076
Thanks very much.

923
01:11:09,346 --> 01:11:12,679
Daddy, will you come on
and finish the story?

924
01:11:13,817 --> 01:11:16,012
Okay, I'm coming. I'm coming.

925
01:11:19,756 --> 01:11:23,089
What happens if the guy drowns?
How do they find him?

926
01:11:23,827 --> 01:11:27,160
When you die, there's bubbles
that come up or something.

927
01:11:27,397 --> 01:11:28,659
Where did I leave off?

928
01:11:28,932 --> 01:11:31,423
You left off right there.

929
01:11:31,668 --> 01:11:33,260
"Thundering typhoons..."

930
01:11:36,006 --> 01:11:38,167
It's got an obstacle course and stuff.

931
01:11:38,408 --> 01:11:40,603
- The cars go really fast.
- How much?

932
01:11:40,844 --> 01:11:41,936
It's really neat.

933
01:11:42,179 --> 01:11:43,612
It's neat.

934
01:11:44,381 --> 01:11:47,077
- Come here, I want you to look...
- Okay, okay.

935
01:12:02,465 --> 01:12:04,797
I'll have him back by 6.

936
01:12:05,802 --> 01:12:07,133
You got so handsome.

937
01:13:03,660 --> 01:13:08,097
Remember, we talked about it,
keep your answers short and succinct.

938
01:13:08,331 --> 01:13:11,767
Just tell the truth and it'll be
all right. Believe me.

939
01:13:14,337 --> 01:13:16,931
- She's here.
- Yeah, I know. I saw her.

940
01:13:17,173 --> 01:13:20,973
Whatever you do, try not to become
emotional, no matter what he says.

941
01:13:21,211 --> 01:13:24,806
You'll hear things that may upset you.
I don't want you to react.

942
01:13:25,282 --> 01:13:29,378
Persons having business with the
Supreme Court, State of New York...

943
01:13:29,686 --> 01:13:33,053
special term part five,
draw nigh and ye shall be heard.

944
01:13:33,290 --> 01:13:38,023
This court is now in session.
Judge Atkins presiding. All rise.

945
01:13:54,978 --> 01:13:58,505
- Is the petitioner's attorney ready?
- I am, Your Honor.

946
01:13:58,748 --> 01:14:00,875
I would like to call Joanna Kramer.

947
01:14:01,184 --> 01:14:02,879
Motherhood, going for the throat.

948
01:14:03,186 --> 01:14:06,053
You swear to tell the truth
and nothing but the truth?

949
01:14:06,323 --> 01:14:07,654
I do.

950
01:14:13,897 --> 01:14:18,095
Now, Mrs. Kramer, would you tell
the court how long you were married?

951
01:14:18,368 --> 01:14:19,528
Eight years.

952
01:14:19,836 --> 01:14:23,101
And would you describe those years
as happy?

953
01:14:23,440 --> 01:14:25,533
The first two, yes.

954
01:14:25,875 --> 01:14:29,367
But after that it became
increasingly difficult.

955
01:14:30,246 --> 01:14:34,615
Mrs. Kramer, did you hold a job
before you were married?

956
01:14:34,851 --> 01:14:38,343
Yes, I did.
When I first got out of Smith...

957
01:14:38,621 --> 01:14:43,615
<i>I worked in the art department of
Mademoiselle magazine for years.</i>

958
01:14:44,527 --> 01:14:48,088
Did you continue to work
after you were married?

959
01:14:48,298 --> 01:14:50,425
No. I did not.

960
01:14:50,700 --> 01:14:52,099
Did you wish to?

961
01:14:52,302 --> 01:14:57,296
Yes, but every time I talked to Ted...

962
01:14:57,540 --> 01:15:02,273
To my ex-husband about it,
he wouldn't listen.

963
01:15:02,579 --> 01:15:07,073
He refused to discuss it
in any serious way.

964
01:15:07,450 --> 01:15:10,010
He said that I
probably couldn't get a job...

965
01:15:10,220 --> 01:15:12,814
that would pay enough
to hire a babysitter.

966
01:15:13,123 --> 01:15:16,058
Tell me, are you employed
at the present time?

967
01:15:16,326 --> 01:15:18,794
I'm a sportswear designer
here in New York.

968
01:15:19,062 --> 01:15:21,553
And what is your present salary?

969
01:15:21,765 --> 01:15:24,393
I make $31,000 a year.

970
01:15:24,801 --> 01:15:28,328
Mrs. Kramer, do you love your child?

971
01:15:29,406 --> 01:15:31,670
Yes, I do, very much.

972
01:15:31,975 --> 01:15:34,808
And yet you chose to leave him.

973
01:15:35,745 --> 01:15:37,144
Yes.

974
01:15:43,353 --> 01:15:46,914
During the last five years
of our marriage...

975
01:15:48,658 --> 01:15:51,183
I was becoming more
and more unhappy.

976
01:15:51,861 --> 01:15:53,294
More and more troubled.

977
01:15:53,530 --> 01:15:57,523
And I really needed
somebody to help me...

978
01:15:57,834 --> 01:16:00,860
but when I turned to Ted, he just...

979
01:16:01,938 --> 01:16:04,031
wasn't there for me.

980
01:16:04,641 --> 01:16:07,439
So we became more isolated
from one another...

981
01:16:07,644 --> 01:16:09,475
more and more separate.

982
01:16:10,146 --> 01:16:12,774
He was very involved in his career.

983
01:16:13,883 --> 01:16:18,013
And because of his attitude
towards my fears...

984
01:16:18,288 --> 01:16:21,724
and his inability
to deal with my feelings...

985
01:16:22,959 --> 01:16:25,393
I had come to have
almost no self-esteem.

986
01:16:26,896 --> 01:16:29,626
I was scared and I was very unhappy.

987
01:16:29,866 --> 01:16:32,334
In my mind I had no choice
but to leave.

988
01:16:34,204 --> 01:16:39,039
At the time I left, I felt that
there was something wrong with me...

989
01:16:39,542 --> 01:16:42,375
and that my son would be
better off without me.

990
01:16:44,147 --> 01:16:48,481
And it was only after I got
to California that I realized...

991
01:16:48,718 --> 01:16:52,814
after getting into therapy,
that I wasn't a terrible person.

992
01:16:55,558 --> 01:17:00,086
And just because I needed some kind
of creative or emotional outlet...

993
01:17:00,363 --> 01:17:03,594
other than my child,
that didn't make me unfit.

994
01:17:04,501 --> 01:17:08,437
I would like to submit in evidence
a report by Mrs. Kramer's therapist...

995
01:17:08,705 --> 01:17:10,195
Dr. Eleanor Freedman.

996
01:17:10,406 --> 01:17:11,566
Objection, Your Honor.

997
01:17:11,841 --> 01:17:15,333
The report is irrelevant
and not binding on the respondent.

998
01:17:15,612 --> 01:17:16,670
Overruled.

999
01:17:18,181 --> 01:17:21,776
Can you tell the court why
you are asking for custody?

1000
01:17:23,620 --> 01:17:25,747
Because he's my child...

1001
01:17:26,222 --> 01:17:28,588
and because I love him.

1002
01:17:30,093 --> 01:17:32,220
I know I left my son.

1003
01:17:33,563 --> 01:17:36,396
I know that
that's a terrible thing to do.

1004
01:17:39,936 --> 01:17:43,463
Believe me, I have to live with that
every day of my life.

1005
01:17:44,040 --> 01:17:46,201
But in order to leave him...

1006
01:17:46,876 --> 01:17:50,141
I had to believe it was
the only thing I could do...

1007
01:17:52,081 --> 01:17:54,379
and that it was
the best thing for him.

1008
01:17:54,651 --> 01:17:57,279
I was incapable of functioning
in that home.

1009
01:17:57,554 --> 01:17:59,545
And I didn't know...

1010
01:17:59,756 --> 01:18:02,054
what the alternative was...

1011
01:18:02,258 --> 01:18:05,489
so I thought it was not best
that I take him with me.

1012
01:18:05,762 --> 01:18:09,391
However, I have since
gotten some help...

1013
01:18:09,632 --> 01:18:14,126
and I have worked very, very hard
to become a whole human being.

1014
01:18:16,906 --> 01:18:19,568
I don't think I should be
punished for that.

1015
01:18:21,244 --> 01:18:24,145
I don't think my little boy
should be punished.

1016
01:18:24,647 --> 01:18:26,911
Billy's only 7 years old.

1017
01:18:27,784 --> 01:18:29,342
He needs me.

1018
01:18:30,286 --> 01:18:33,119
I'm not saying he doesn't
need his father...

1019
01:18:34,424 --> 01:18:37,086
but I really believe
he needs me more.

1020
01:18:38,962 --> 01:18:43,365
I was his mommy
for five and a half years...

1021
01:18:44,267 --> 01:18:48,328
and Ted took over that role
for 18 months.

1022
01:18:52,675 --> 01:18:55,542
But I don't know how anybody
can possibly believe...

1023
01:18:55,812 --> 01:18:59,839
that I have less of a stake
in mothering that little boy...

1024
01:19:00,149 --> 01:19:02,310
than Mr. Kramer does.

1025
01:19:05,722 --> 01:19:07,349
I'm his mother.

1026
01:19:09,792 --> 01:19:11,487
I'm his mother.

1027
01:19:16,899 --> 01:19:17,957
Thank you, Mrs. Kramer.

1028
01:19:18,368 --> 01:19:20,461
I have no further questions.

1029
01:19:22,538 --> 01:19:25,029
Now then, Mrs. Kramer...

1030
01:19:25,875 --> 01:19:30,471
you say that you were married
for eight years, is that correct?

1031
01:19:32,582 --> 01:19:37,713
In all that time did your husband ever
strike you or physically abuse you?

1032
01:19:38,921 --> 01:19:40,149
No.

1033
01:19:40,356 --> 01:19:45,259
Did he ever strike or physically
abuse his child in any way?

1034
01:19:46,763 --> 01:19:49,857
Would you describe your husband
as an alcoholic?

1035
01:19:51,267 --> 01:19:52,757
A heavy drinker?

1036
01:19:53,703 --> 01:19:55,534
Was he unfaithful?

1037
01:20:02,912 --> 01:20:05,904
Did he ever fail
to provide for you in any way?

1038
01:20:08,418 --> 01:20:10,886
I can certainly see why you left him.

1039
01:20:11,120 --> 01:20:12,587
Objection.

1040
01:20:14,857 --> 01:20:17,792
How long do you plan to live
in New York, Mrs. Kramer?

1041
01:20:18,227 --> 01:20:19,717
Permanently.

1042
01:20:21,464 --> 01:20:24,365
How many boyfriends have you had,
permanently?

1043
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:26,864
Objection on grounds of vagueness.

1044
01:20:27,070 --> 01:20:28,435
I'll allow it.

1045
01:20:32,575 --> 01:20:33,633
I don't recall.

1046
01:20:34,110 --> 01:20:36,578
More than three, less than 33,
permanently?

1047
01:20:36,813 --> 01:20:38,144
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1048
01:20:38,414 --> 01:20:40,575
The witness will answer, please.

1049
01:20:42,652 --> 01:20:44,313
Somewhere in between.

1050
01:20:44,587 --> 01:20:46,145
Do you have a lover now?

1051
01:20:50,159 --> 01:20:53,925
Your Honor, I would request a direct
answer to a direct question.

1052
01:20:54,163 --> 01:20:55,960
Does she have a lover?

1053
01:20:56,265 --> 01:20:59,928
I'll allow that.
The witness will answer, please.

1054
01:21:01,671 --> 01:21:03,901
Yes, I'm seeing someone now.

1055
01:21:04,173 --> 01:21:06,903
Is that... permanent?

1056
01:21:08,745 --> 01:21:09,803
I don't know.

1057
01:21:10,012 --> 01:21:12,572
We don't know
when you say permanently...

1058
01:21:12,849 --> 01:21:17,115
if you plan to live in New York,
or keep your child, for that matter...

1059
01:21:17,320 --> 01:21:22,121
since you've never done anything
that could be regarded as permanent.

1060
01:21:22,325 --> 01:21:26,694
Objection. I request the counsel be
prevented from harassing the witness.

1061
01:21:26,963 --> 01:21:28,157
Sustained.

1062
01:21:28,431 --> 01:21:30,797
I'll put it another way, counselor.

1063
01:21:31,367 --> 01:21:35,098
What was the longest personal
relationship in your life...

1064
01:21:35,304 --> 01:21:37,932
outside of parents or girlfriends?

1065
01:21:40,343 --> 01:21:42,038
I suppose that would be my child.

1066
01:21:42,712 --> 01:21:45,374
Whom you've seen twice in a year.

1067
01:21:45,615 --> 01:21:49,346
Mrs. Kramer, your ex-husband...

1068
01:21:49,619 --> 01:21:53,316
wasn't he the longest
personal relationship in your life?

1069
01:21:56,859 --> 01:21:59,157
Would you speak up?
I couldn't hear you.

1070
01:22:00,196 --> 01:22:01,458
Yes.

1071
01:22:01,964 --> 01:22:03,556
How long was that?

1072
01:22:05,067 --> 01:22:08,332
We were married a year
before the baby...

1073
01:22:09,071 --> 01:22:10,538
and seven years after.

1074
01:22:10,807 --> 01:22:14,573
So you were a failure at the most
important relationship in your life.

1075
01:22:14,811 --> 01:22:16,472
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1076
01:22:16,679 --> 01:22:19,648
The witness's opinion on this
is relevant.

1077
01:22:20,516 --> 01:22:22,313
I was not a failure.

1078
01:22:22,985 --> 01:22:26,421
What do you call it, a success?
The marriage ended in divorce.

1079
01:22:26,989 --> 01:22:29,389
I consider it less my failure
than his.

1080
01:22:29,592 --> 01:22:31,150
Congratulations.

1081
01:22:31,360 --> 01:22:35,228
You've just rewritten matrimonial law.
You were both divorced.

1082
01:22:35,431 --> 01:22:36,921
Objection!

1083
01:22:37,767 --> 01:22:41,259
Your Honor, I would like to ask
what this model of stability...

1084
01:22:41,571 --> 01:22:43,835
and respectability
has ever succeeded at.

1085
01:22:44,440 --> 01:22:49,275
Were you a failure at the one most
important relationship in your life?

1086
01:22:51,514 --> 01:22:56,611
- It did not succeed.
- Not it, Mrs. Kramer, you.

1087
01:22:56,919 --> 01:23:01,413
Were you a failure at the one most
important relationship in your life?

1088
01:23:01,691 --> 01:23:03,181
Were you?!

1089
01:23:08,798 --> 01:23:10,060
<i>No.</i>

1090
01:23:15,438 --> 01:23:17,269
Is that a yes, Mrs. Kramer?

1091
01:23:24,747 --> 01:23:26,544
No further questions.

1092
01:23:30,553 --> 01:23:33,488
- Did you have to be so rough?
- Do you want the kid?

1093
01:23:33,789 --> 01:23:35,051
Daddy?

1094
01:23:35,958 --> 01:23:37,220
Daddy.

1095
01:23:37,560 --> 01:23:40,495
- Yeah?
- What did you do when you were little?

1096
01:23:40,730 --> 01:23:42,129
The same things you do.

1097
01:23:42,431 --> 01:23:44,831
<i>Did you watch The Brady Bunch?</i>

1098
01:23:45,434 --> 01:23:47,959
No, we didn't have any television.

1099
01:23:48,471 --> 01:23:50,063
You didn't?

1100
01:23:50,339 --> 01:23:52,068
We listened to the radio.

1101
01:23:52,308 --> 01:23:53,741
What else didn't you have?

1102
01:23:54,176 --> 01:23:55,939
We didn't have lots of things.

1103
01:23:56,145 --> 01:23:58,170
- Like?
- Like a lot of things.

1104
01:23:59,282 --> 01:24:00,340
What kind?

1105
01:24:03,419 --> 01:24:04,852
Come here.

1106
01:24:06,022 --> 01:24:07,649
We didn't have diet soda.

1107
01:24:07,924 --> 01:24:10,085
We had egg creams, which was
chocolate syrup...

1108
01:24:10,326 --> 01:24:12,794
seltzer water and a bit of
milk and you went...

1109
01:24:13,195 --> 01:24:15,993
and you drank it
and it was delicious.

1110
01:24:16,198 --> 01:24:18,689
We didn't have the Mets,
but we had the Brooklyn Dodgers.

1111
01:24:18,935 --> 01:24:21,870
We had the Polo Grounds
and Ebbets Field...

1112
01:24:22,104 --> 01:24:24,038
Boy, those were the days.

1113
01:24:24,273 --> 01:24:26,332
We didn't have the Volkswagens...

1114
01:24:26,542 --> 01:24:30,171
but we had all those different cars
with funny names on them.

1115
01:24:30,379 --> 01:24:32,813
We didn't have Burger King
or McDonald's.

1116
01:24:33,115 --> 01:24:37,381
We had automats where you put a
quarter in and you'd get...

1117
01:24:37,687 --> 01:24:41,179
a piece of pie or a sandwich
you could see through a window.

1118
01:24:41,390 --> 01:24:44,359
We didn't have graffiti,
but we had this guy Kilroy...

1119
01:24:44,994 --> 01:24:47,224
<i>Mr. Kramer is a very devoted father.</i>

1120
01:24:47,496 --> 01:24:50,294
<i>He spends a great deal of time
with Billy.</i>

1121
01:24:50,900 --> 01:24:52,492
He reads to Billy a lot.

1122
01:24:52,702 --> 01:24:56,365
They play together,
they talk all the time.

1123
01:24:57,206 --> 01:24:58,901
He's a wonderful father.

1124
01:24:59,175 --> 01:25:02,008
Thank you.
No further questions.

1125
01:25:02,244 --> 01:25:05,372
Mrs. Phelps, how long
have you known Joanna Kramer?

1126
01:25:05,748 --> 01:25:09,650
About six years, ever since she and
Ted moved into the building.

1127
01:25:09,885 --> 01:25:13,480
How often did you see
Joanna Kramer and her son?

1128
01:25:13,990 --> 01:25:18,222
I haven't seen them together now for
about a year and a half, but...

1129
01:25:18,427 --> 01:25:21,590
back then I saw them two or
three times a week.

1130
01:25:21,931 --> 01:25:24,525
My oldest daughter and Billy
play together.

1131
01:25:24,734 --> 01:25:28,898
Can you describe the relationship
between Joanna Kramer and her son?

1132
01:25:29,171 --> 01:25:30,171
It was good.

1133
01:25:30,606 --> 01:25:32,335
Joanna was a very good mother.

1134
01:25:32,575 --> 01:25:34,634
Both Ted and Joanna are very...

1135
01:25:34,844 --> 01:25:38,075
Did Mrs. Kramer discuss her
relationship with her ex-husband?

1136
01:25:38,848 --> 01:25:40,179
Yes.

1137
01:25:40,449 --> 01:25:43,282
Can you tell the court
exactly what she said?

1138
01:25:45,087 --> 01:25:47,248
Joanna wasn't happy
for many reasons...

1139
01:25:47,523 --> 01:25:52,051
Did you ever hear her say Mr. Kramer
was insensitive to his son's needs?

1140
01:25:56,065 --> 01:25:58,556
Would you answer the question?

1141
01:25:59,568 --> 01:26:02,093
- I didn't hear you.
- Yes, but that was before...

1142
01:26:02,438 --> 01:26:05,032
Did you ever encourage
her to leave her husband?

1143
01:26:05,474 --> 01:26:06,805
No, I did not.

1144
01:26:09,612 --> 01:26:13,139
Several days before she left,
did you say to her:

1145
01:26:13,382 --> 01:26:17,478
"If you're in this much pain,
you owe it to yourself to leave"?

1146
01:26:19,255 --> 01:26:22,053
- I didn't think Joanna...
- Did you say to her:

1147
01:26:22,258 --> 01:26:25,591
"If you're in this much pain,
you owe it to yourself to leave"?

1148
01:26:26,929 --> 01:26:30,092
- Yes, but she was my friend...
- No further questions.

1149
01:26:31,467 --> 01:26:33,594
Mrs. Phelps, you may step down.

1150
01:26:33,836 --> 01:26:36,430
Joanna, things are not the same now.

1151
01:26:36,839 --> 01:26:38,272
Ted is not the same man.

1152
01:26:38,507 --> 01:26:41,305
- You don't know how hard he's tried...
- Mrs. Phelps!

1153
01:26:41,510 --> 01:26:43,410
They're beautiful together.

1154
01:26:43,646 --> 01:26:45,477
The witness is asked to step down.

1155
01:26:45,681 --> 01:26:47,581
If you could see them together...

1156
01:26:47,783 --> 01:26:49,683
maybe you wouldn't be here now.

1157
01:26:49,919 --> 01:26:51,910
Mrs. Phelps, that will be all!

1158
01:26:57,593 --> 01:26:58,992
I'm sorry.

1159
01:27:01,497 --> 01:27:02,828
When you were talking...

1160
01:27:03,632 --> 01:27:08,365
When my ex-wife was talking about how
unhappy she was during our marriage...

1161
01:27:08,604 --> 01:27:11,266
most of what she said
was probably true.

1162
01:27:11,474 --> 01:27:13,772
There's a lot I didn't understand.

1163
01:27:14,510 --> 01:27:17,138
There's a lot
I'd do different if I could...

1164
01:27:17,513 --> 01:27:20,676
just like there's a lot you wish
you could change but can't.

1165
01:27:20,883 --> 01:27:24,216
Some things, once they're done,
can't be undone.

1166
01:27:25,354 --> 01:27:26,981
My wife...

1167
01:27:27,323 --> 01:27:32,158
My ex-wife says she loves Billy
and I believe she does.

1168
01:27:32,995 --> 01:27:35,520
But I don't think
that's the issue here.

1169
01:27:36,565 --> 01:27:38,658
If I understand it correctly...

1170
01:27:39,535 --> 01:27:43,232
what means the most here is
what's best for our son.

1171
01:27:43,739 --> 01:27:46,139
What's best for Billy.

1172
01:27:47,209 --> 01:27:49,074
My wife used to say to me:

1173
01:27:49,311 --> 01:27:52,542
"Why can't a woman have
the same ambitions as a man?"

1174
01:27:53,082 --> 01:27:54,674
I think you're right.

1175
01:27:54,984 --> 01:27:57,214
And maybe I've learned that much.

1176
01:27:57,419 --> 01:27:59,819
By the same token, I'd like to know...

1177
01:28:00,055 --> 01:28:05,015
what law says a woman is a better
parent simply by virtue of her sex?

1178
01:28:05,828 --> 01:28:08,991
I've had time to think about
what makes a good parent.

1179
01:28:09,265 --> 01:28:12,166
It has to do with constancy.
It has to do with patience...

1180
01:28:12,368 --> 01:28:13,892
listening to him...

1181
01:28:14,170 --> 01:28:16,832
or pretending to listen
when you can't anymore.

1182
01:28:17,072 --> 01:28:20,337
It has to do with love,
like she was saying.

1183
01:28:20,676 --> 01:28:24,578
I don't know where it says a woman
has a corner on that market...

1184
01:28:24,780 --> 01:28:28,045
that a man has any less
of those emotions than a woman.

1185
01:28:28,284 --> 01:28:31,583
Billy has a home with me.
I've made it the best I could.

1186
01:28:31,854 --> 01:28:34,687
It's not perfect.
I'm not a perfect parent.

1187
01:28:34,924 --> 01:28:37,484
Sometimes I don't
have enough patience

1188
01:28:37,660 --> 01:28:39,924
and I forget that he's a little kid.

1189
01:28:40,296 --> 01:28:41,695
But I'm there.

1190
01:28:43,399 --> 01:28:47,563
We eat breakfast and he talks to me,
and then we go to school.

1191
01:28:47,770 --> 01:28:52,070
At night we have dinner together and
we talk and I read to him and...

1192
01:28:53,375 --> 01:28:57,038
And we built a life together
and we love each other.

1193
01:29:04,086 --> 01:29:06,054
If you destroy that...

1194
01:29:07,590 --> 01:29:09,956
it may be irreparable.

1195
01:29:17,833 --> 01:29:20,825
Joanna, don't do that, please.

1196
01:29:22,571 --> 01:29:25,802
- Don't do it twice to him.
- Thank you, Mr. Kramer.

1197
01:29:26,108 --> 01:29:27,666
No further questions.

1198
01:29:29,511 --> 01:29:31,911
How long have you
worked in advertising?

1199
01:29:32,147 --> 01:29:34,411
Ever since I graduated high school.

1200
01:29:35,684 --> 01:29:38,983
College, I mean.
I've been there about 15 years.

1201
01:29:39,388 --> 01:29:43,188
Would you say you've achieved a
certain status in your profession?

1202
01:29:43,392 --> 01:29:45,451
Yes, I have a good reputation.

1203
01:29:45,728 --> 01:29:49,357
When you worked at Roth, Kane
and Donovan, what was your salary?

1204
01:29:49,565 --> 01:29:51,692
Around $33,000 dollars a year
when I left.

1205
01:29:51,934 --> 01:29:54,562
Now you work at Norman, Craig
and Kummel?

1206
01:29:54,770 --> 01:29:56,761
- Yes.
- What is your salary?

1207
01:29:57,373 --> 01:29:59,568
It's almost 29,000.

1208
01:29:59,775 --> 01:30:02,209
Could you be more specific?

1209
01:30:02,544 --> 01:30:04,774
I make $28,200.

1210
01:30:05,214 --> 01:30:07,205
28,200.

1211
01:30:07,816 --> 01:30:12,253
You're the only person who's working
his way down the ladder of success.

1212
01:30:12,454 --> 01:30:16,982
Objection. Your Honor, I ask that
counsel's last remark be stricken.

1213
01:30:17,293 --> 01:30:18,293
Sustained.

1214
01:30:18,427 --> 01:30:21,055
Is it true you were fired
from your previous job?

1215
01:30:21,330 --> 01:30:25,926
- I was let go.
- Will you tell us why you were let go?

1216
01:30:26,402 --> 01:30:28,632
There was a difference
of opinion in policy.

1217
01:30:28,937 --> 01:30:33,499
Is it true your agency lost a major
account due to your negligence?

1218
01:30:33,976 --> 01:30:34,976
Objection!

1219
01:30:35,010 --> 01:30:37,808
I'm trying to establish
the witness's employment record.

1220
01:30:38,080 --> 01:30:40,412
He cannot hold a job.

1221
01:30:40,683 --> 01:30:42,241
I'll allow it, Mr. Shaunessy.

1222
01:30:43,319 --> 01:30:46,482
It's not unusual in advertising
for a client...

1223
01:30:46,755 --> 01:30:48,950
to change his mind
and go elsewhere...

1224
01:30:49,825 --> 01:30:53,488
Was it true you walked out on a
client during a major presentation...

1225
01:30:53,829 --> 01:30:56,855
saying that you had an appointment
with a teacher?

1226
01:30:57,132 --> 01:31:00,192
My son was sitting next to a kid
who was hitting and biting.

1227
01:31:00,469 --> 01:31:03,131
- Yes or no?
- Yes, but he bit my kid.

1228
01:31:03,439 --> 01:31:07,535
Last spring, did you miss a deadline
on the Mid-Atlantic account...

1229
01:31:07,776 --> 01:31:10,336
causing your company a
great deal of embarrassment...

1230
01:31:10,546 --> 01:31:12,537
and considerable
financial liability?

1231
01:31:12,781 --> 01:31:15,545
On that day I had to go home
because my child was sick.

1232
01:31:15,784 --> 01:31:18,344
Did you or did you not
miss a deadline?

1233
01:31:18,620 --> 01:31:20,713
- My son was sick.
- Answer the question.

1234
01:31:20,989 --> 01:31:24,186
I'm trying to answer the question.
It's not yes or no.

1235
01:31:25,127 --> 01:31:27,357
- Yes or no?
- He had a 104 temperature!

1236
01:31:27,563 --> 01:31:30,157
He's lying there sweating!
I go home to him!

1237
01:31:30,799 --> 01:31:35,236
Mr. Kramer, I urge you to stop
or I'll have to hold you in contempt.

1238
01:31:41,310 --> 01:31:42,902
I missed the deadline.

1239
01:31:43,746 --> 01:31:46,579
- Do you have a violent temper?
- No.

1240
01:31:46,849 --> 01:31:48,817
- Objection.
- I withdraw the question.

1241
01:31:49,017 --> 01:31:52,043
- Do you consider yourself a fit parent?
- Yes, I do.

1242
01:31:52,321 --> 01:31:55,256
Is it true your child nearly lost
an eye while in your care?

1243
01:31:55,557 --> 01:31:57,115
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1244
01:31:57,326 --> 01:31:58,816
Answer the question.

1245
01:31:59,094 --> 01:32:01,324
He was in the playground,
on the jungle gym...

1246
01:32:01,597 --> 01:32:04,566
And fell and nearly lost an eye
while in your care.

1247
01:32:04,767 --> 01:32:06,098
He fell and cut himself.

1248
01:32:06,335 --> 01:32:07,927
Is it true you told your ex-wife...

1249
01:32:08,170 --> 01:32:11,867
you were responsible for the
injury that disfigured your child?

1250
01:32:12,174 --> 01:32:13,368
Did you tell her:

1251
01:32:13,842 --> 01:32:17,175
"When it happened I felt guilty.
I felt it was my fault"?

1252
01:32:17,413 --> 01:32:20,405
- Objection!
- I have concluded my questions.

1253
01:32:56,285 --> 01:32:57,309
Ted?

1254
01:32:58,921 --> 01:33:00,320
Ted?

1255
01:33:05,327 --> 01:33:10,390
I'm sorry. I mentioned the accident
to him two months ago...

1256
01:33:10,599 --> 01:33:13,659
and I never thought he would
bring it up, never.

1257
01:33:15,237 --> 01:33:16,602
Believe me.

1258
01:33:17,506 --> 01:33:21,806
I never would have mentioned it if
I thought he'd pull a thing like that.

1259
01:33:22,845 --> 01:33:24,107
I'm sorry.

1260
01:33:24,513 --> 01:33:25,810
I'm...

1261
01:33:37,292 --> 01:33:38,316
Ted.

1262
01:33:38,594 --> 01:33:40,619
- Hi.
- Hi. Here, let me help you.

1263
01:33:40,829 --> 01:33:42,091
Heard anything yet?

1264
01:33:42,331 --> 01:33:45,198
Any day. My lawyer says
no news is good news.

1265
01:33:45,501 --> 01:33:47,093
- Guess what.
- What?

1266
01:33:47,336 --> 01:33:49,930
Charley and I are talking about
getting back together.

1267
01:33:50,138 --> 01:33:52,834
Really?
Did he finally call you?

1268
01:33:53,041 --> 01:33:54,599
No, I called him.

1269
01:33:54,877 --> 01:33:56,003
How come?

1270
01:33:56,278 --> 01:34:00,442
I don't know. I got to thinking
about a lot of things since the trial.

1271
01:34:00,682 --> 01:34:01,682
And...

1272
01:34:02,451 --> 01:34:05,181
I don't think it'll work out,
but he seems to want it.

1273
01:34:05,454 --> 01:34:08,719
That's terrific.
How do you feel?

1274
01:34:08,957 --> 01:34:12,484
I don't know.
I feel scared, I guess.

1275
01:34:22,738 --> 01:34:24,672
- Hi.
- Hi.

1276
01:34:27,175 --> 01:34:28,472
I lost.

1277
01:34:29,811 --> 01:34:32,075
I can't tell you how sorry I am.

1278
01:34:41,023 --> 01:34:42,320
What happened?

1279
01:34:43,659 --> 01:34:46,992
The judge went for motherhood
right down the line.

1280
01:34:47,996 --> 01:34:52,160
"Ordered and decreed that the
petitioner be awarded custody..."

1281
01:34:52,434 --> 01:34:54,698
effective Monday,
the 23rd of January...

1282
01:34:55,070 --> 01:34:59,939
that the respondent pay for the
support of the child, $400 a month.

1283
01:35:00,208 --> 01:35:02,733
The father shall have the
following visitation rights:

1284
01:35:03,045 --> 01:35:06,742
Every other weekend, one night a
week to be mutually agreed upon...

1285
01:35:07,049 --> 01:35:09,847
"and one half of the child's
vacation period."

1286
01:35:10,085 --> 01:35:12,349
- That's it.
- What if I fight it?

1287
01:35:12,554 --> 01:35:14,419
I can't guarantee anything.

1288
01:35:14,623 --> 01:35:16,022
I'll take my chances.

1289
01:35:16,291 --> 01:35:18,589
- It'll cost you.
- I'll pay anything.

1290
01:35:19,294 --> 01:35:21,922
Look, Ted, I have to
tell you something.

1291
01:35:23,265 --> 01:35:25,961
This time it'll be Billy that pays.

1292
01:35:26,201 --> 01:35:28,294
I'll have to put him on the stand.

1293
01:35:28,770 --> 01:35:30,465
I can't do that.

1294
01:35:30,772 --> 01:35:32,763
No, I don't want to do that.

1295
01:35:35,544 --> 01:35:38,308
Thanks very much for your time.
I'm gonna take a walk.

1296
01:35:54,663 --> 01:35:57,154
Ted? It's me.

1297
01:36:02,471 --> 01:36:03,631
Ted?

1298
01:36:04,172 --> 01:36:05,730
I just heard.

1299
01:36:06,141 --> 01:36:07,802
Please go away.

1300
01:36:08,944 --> 01:36:10,935
Are you okay?

1301
01:36:12,514 --> 01:36:16,143
I just have to be by myself
for a while, Margaret.

1302
01:36:23,792 --> 01:36:24,850
I don't understand.

1303
01:36:25,160 --> 01:36:28,095
The problem is your mom and I
both want you to live with us.

1304
01:36:28,330 --> 01:36:32,664
So that's why we decided to go see
this man, who is the judge...

1305
01:36:32,868 --> 01:36:36,326
and we let him decide because
he's very wise and experienced.

1306
01:36:36,538 --> 01:36:40,167
We talked to him for a few days
and then asked what he thought.

1307
01:36:40,442 --> 01:36:42,706
You know what?
He agreed with Mommy.

1308
01:36:42,944 --> 01:36:46,505
He thought it'd be terrific
if you lived with her from now on.

1309
01:36:46,782 --> 01:36:50,218
I'm lucky because I get to have
dinner with you once a week.

1310
01:36:50,485 --> 01:36:53,477
And twice a month
we spend the weekends together.

1311
01:36:55,057 --> 01:36:58,288
Where's my bed gonna be?
Where am I gonna sleep?

1312
01:36:58,660 --> 01:37:02,721
Mommy's figured that all out. You
have your own bedroom at her place.

1313
01:37:04,199 --> 01:37:06,690
- Where will all my toys be?
- At Mommy's.

1314
01:37:06,902 --> 01:37:09,166
We're gonna take
all your toys over there.

1315
01:37:09,371 --> 01:37:12,465
If you play your cards right,
she'll buy you some new ones.

1316
01:37:13,575 --> 01:37:15,873
Who's gonna read me
my bedtime stories?

1317
01:37:16,311 --> 01:37:17,869
Mommy will.

1318
01:37:18,580 --> 01:37:21,071
You're not gonna kiss me
good night anymore?

1319
01:37:21,349 --> 01:37:23,579
No, I won't be able to do that.

1320
01:37:23,819 --> 01:37:27,255
But, you know, I get to visit.

1321
01:37:29,825 --> 01:37:32,350
It's gonna be okay. Really.

1322
01:37:32,561 --> 01:37:35,052
If I don't like it, can I come home?

1323
01:37:35,263 --> 01:37:36,855
What do you mean?

1324
01:37:37,099 --> 01:37:39,260
You'll have a great time with Mommy.

1325
01:37:39,501 --> 01:37:41,867
Really. She loves you so much.

1326
01:37:42,404 --> 01:37:43,735
Dad?

1327
01:37:44,773 --> 01:37:48,334
Don't forget, once, if you can
just call me up, okay?

1328
01:37:54,850 --> 01:37:56,681
We're gonna be okay.

1329
01:38:01,523 --> 01:38:03,616
Let's go get some ice cream.

1330
01:39:43,325 --> 01:39:46,158
Come on, let's get
this show on the road.

1331
01:39:48,196 --> 01:39:50,164
Let's get a little hustle now, okay?

1332
01:39:50,365 --> 01:39:52,162
Come on, set the table.

1333
01:40:00,842 --> 01:40:02,036
Come on.

1334
01:40:13,722 --> 01:40:15,155
Are you ready?

1335
01:40:33,575 --> 01:40:34,575
Yes?

1336
01:40:34,676 --> 01:40:37,270
<i>It's Joanna.
I'm downstairs in the lobby.</i>

1337
01:40:37,512 --> 01:40:39,946
<i>Can you come down here
and meet me alone?</i>

1338
01:40:47,022 --> 01:40:48,022
Hi.

1339
01:40:49,391 --> 01:40:50,585
What's up?

1340
01:40:55,030 --> 01:40:57,294
Tell me. What?
What's the matter?

1341
01:40:58,033 --> 01:40:59,967
I woke up this morning.

1342
01:41:03,905 --> 01:41:05,805
Kept thinking about Billy...

1343
01:41:06,074 --> 01:41:09,043
and I was thinking about
him waking up in his room...

1344
01:41:09,244 --> 01:41:12,042
with his little clouds
all around that I painted...

1345
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:17,047
and I thought I should have
painted clouds downtown because...

1346
01:41:18,720 --> 01:41:22,315
then he would think that
he was waking up at home.

1347
01:41:25,560 --> 01:41:28,757
I came here to take my son home.

1348
01:41:33,001 --> 01:41:35,435
And I realized he already is home.

1349
01:41:41,810 --> 01:41:44,244
I love him very much.

1350
01:41:49,617 --> 01:41:51,915
I'm not gonna take him with me.

1351
01:42:00,829 --> 01:42:03,696
Can I go up and talk to him?

1352
01:42:04,032 --> 01:42:05,158
Yeah.

1353
01:42:13,274 --> 01:42:16,710
Why don't you go upstairs
and see him and I'll wait here.

1354
01:42:28,123 --> 01:42:29,647
How do I look?

1355
01:42:31,793 --> 01:42:32,793
Terrific.


